Don't get fooled by the cartoonish style and low res graphics. This is a game that needs to  be played in order to be understood. Let me tell that even if it is an indie  game it has some major pros:
-the art is, for a pixelated game, very pretty and the background as well;
-it is a "horror" pixel game, if you couldn't tell from the description but no major scares, unless you are a faint of heart >:D
-I love how it reminds me of old fairy tales like Rumplestilskin (hope I wrote that name corectly) with the whole 'Guess my name' sort of thing;
-every decision shapes the story; there are 5 endings and that is AWESOME;
However the are some cons which I can't overlook since you will pay 10$ for it:
-the speed of the hero is so SLOOOOOOooooooooooW; I mean there are a lot of places to go and at that pace it will take a lot of time, for me it took 5 hours to complete the major endings;
-the scares aren't so spoopy, I got scared more of the goats than the, ahem, monsters;
-the sprites could have been a little bit more polished but, meh, who am I to judge;
Just to be honest with you guys, I bought it on sale and I payed like, $3, so I can't say that it really is a game worth 10$ but for the price I payed I was pleasantly surprised. So if you're looking for a game that sends you back to your childhood bed time stories than this is a game for you!

